# Dropdown Management (0910)

## Overview
This document outlines the role-based dropdown management system for Discipline and Template Type selectors in the Construct AI platform.

## **CRITICAL: Discipline Dropdown Access Control Rules** 🔐

### **🚨 IMPORTANT PERMISSION SEPARATION**

This document outlines **modal dropdown permissions** - the disciplines users can select when creating/editing templates in modals. **These are SEPARATE from accordion navigation permissions**, which control where users can go in the application.

#### **What This Document Controls (Modal Dropdowns):**
- ✅ What disciplines appear in modal discipline dropdowns
- ✅ What template types users can create in modals
- ✅ What disciplines users can assign to templates/forms during creation

#### **What This Document DOES NOT Control (Accordion Navigation):**
- ❌ Which accordion sections users can click/navigate to
- ❌ Which pages users can access through the sidebar
- ❌ Which application areas users can enter directly

**See the main application architecture documentation for accordion navigation permissions.**

### **CORE ACCESS PRINCIPLES** (Required in All Documentation)

#### **Governance Team Users (Full Access)**
- **✅ Can access ALL disciplines** via dropdowns: Civil Engineering, Procurement, HSSE Safety, Governance
- **✅ Full template creation rights** across all discipline types
- **✅ Administrative permissions** for managing document types across organizations
- **Scope**: See all disciplines regardless of navigation path or accordion section

#### **Discipline-Specific Users (Limited Access)**
- **❌ Limited to their assigned discipline only** (e.g., Procurement users see only Procurement)
- **❌ Cannot create templates** for other disciplines
- **❌ Read-only access** to published templates from other disciplines
- **Scope**: See only their discipline templates regardless of navigation path

### **CRITICAL IMPLEMENTATION RULE** ⚠️
**All modals **MUST** respect these access rules:**
- Governance users: `ALL_DISCIPLINES_AVAILABLE`
- Non-governance users: `ONLY_ASSIGNED_DISCIPLINE_VISIBLE`
- **Violation breaks system security and tenant isolation**

### **🎯 Modal-Specific Permission Examples**

#### **CreateNewTemplateModal** (Recently Enhanced)
- **Governance Users**: Can select any discipline (Civil Engineering, Procurement, HSSE Safety, Electrical, etc.)
- **Discipline Users**: Can only select their assigned discipline (e.g., Procurement users see only "Procurement")
- **Purpose**: Template creation with role-appropriate discipline selection

#### **AITemplateModal** (Already Correctly Implemented)
- **Governance Users**: Can select any discipline for AI template generation
- **Discipline Users**: Can only select their assigned discipline
- **Purpose**: AI-powered template creation with proper access controls

#### **Template Management Mode**: List View
- **Governance Users**: See templates from ALL disciplines they can access
- **Discipline Users**: See only templates from their assigned discipline
- **Purpose**: Discipline-appropriate template management

### Role-Based Access Control

### User Roles and Permissions

#### Governance Team Users
- **Can access all disciplines:** Civil Engineering, Procurement, HSSE Safety, Governance
- **Full template creation rights** across all discipline types
- **Administrative permissions** for managing document types

#### Discipline-Specific Users
- **Limited to assigned discipline only** (typically Governance/01300)
- **Cannot create templates** for other disciplines
- **Read-only access** to published templates from other disciplines

### Dropdown Behaviors

#### Discipline Dropdown
- **For Governance Users:** Shows all available disciplines
- **For Other Users:** Shows only their assigned discipline (Governance/01300)
- **Dynamic filtering:** Updates available template types based on selected discipline

#### Template Type Dropdown
- **Dependent on discipline selection**
- **Dynamically loaded** from `document_types_by_discipline` table
- **Filtered by user role** through `getTemplateTypeOptions()` function
- **Disabled state** when no discipline is selected

### Implementation Details

#### Key Functions
```javascript
// Returns disciplines available to the current user
getUserAssignableDisciplines()

// Returns template types for a specific discipline
getTemplateTypeOptions(selectedDiscipline)
```

#### Modal Implementations (All 6 Modals)
- **CreateNewTemplateModal** (`modals/CreateNewTemplateModal.js`): Role-based discipline and template type filtering - Governance users see all disciplines, others see limited disciplines
- **AITemplateModal** (`components/modals/AITemplateModal.jsx`): AI-powered template generation with restricted discipline selection based on user role
- **BuildTemplateModal** (`modals/BuildTemplateModal.js`): Template building interface hardcoded to Governance discipline (01300)
- **ManageDocumentTypesModal** (`modals/ManageDocumentTypesModal.js`): Administrative interface for managing document types across disciplines
- **TemplateModal** (`components/modals/TemplateModal.jsx`): Generic template management interface with discipline-aware filtering
- **BulkTemplateCopyModal** (`components/modals/BulkTemplateCopyModal.jsx`): Bulk template operations with discipline-appropriate copying permissions

### Security Considerations

#### Data Filtering
- All dropdown data is filtered server-side through API queries
- Client-side filtering provides UI responsiveness only
- Database-level RLS (Row Level Security) policies enforce data access

#### User Context Validation
- User role is determined on page load and cached
- Development bypass available for testing purposes
- Authentication tokens validated on each API call

### Testing and Validation

#### Test Cases
1. **Governance User:** Can see all disciplines and template types
2. **Discipline User:** Limited to assigned discipline only
3. **Discipline Selection:** Template types update when discipline changes
4. **Template Creation:** Only allowed disciplines appear in dropdowns

#### Error Handling
- Graceful fallback to basic options when API unavailable
- Clear error messages for permission denied scenarios
- Loading states during data fetching

